THABA NCHU Six people died in a multiple-vehicle crash on the N8 between Thaba Nchu and Botshabelo in the Free State early on Sunday, the Road Traffic Management Corporation (RTMC) said.The crash involved five vehicles and reports indicated that two vehicles initially collided head-on, killing five people, RTMC spokesman Simon Zwane said.READ: Five killed in horror Durban crash This set off a chain of events in which three other vehicles were involved in crashes on the same scene. The third vehicle drove through the scene and collided with the debris. The fourth vehicle slowed down to avoid the scene but the fifth vehicle could not stop and drove into the rear of the vehicle, killing one person."The RTMC and the South African Police [Service] are investigating the cause of the crash, he said.The accident further highlighted the dangers of driving in the early hours of the morning, Zwane said An analysis of major crashes showed these frequently occurred towards midnight and in the early hours of the morning.Weekends were particularly dangerous as more crashes occurred on Friday, Saturday, Sunday, and Monday than on other days of the week, Zwane said.African News Agency